item.name: tjwagner
item.message: VAD stands for Velocity Azimuth Display, and is named for finding the velocity along specific azimuths, then doing the Pythagorean math to convert that into a two dimensional wind vector. All that math is done for you, so you can just play with the velocities that come out of it.
